# StandardModel.QuantumNumbers

Quantum number types and conventions.

Each Standard Model particle is characterized by quantum numbers under
G_SM = SU(3)_c × SU(2)_L × U(1)_Y. The relevant quantum numbers are:

- Isospin T (SU(2) representation label)
- Third component T₃ (eigenvalue of diagonal SU(2) generator)
- Hypercharge Y (U(1)_Y charge)
- Color (SU(3) representation)
- Electric charge Q = T₃ + Y/2

Convention: hypercharge normalization Q = T₃ + Y/2.
Provenance: clean-room from Weinberg, "The Quantum Theory of Fields", Vol. 2.

Status: stub — quantum number types and consistency lemmas to be defined.
